  "title": "IT Assistant / System Support Officer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities </strong></u></p><p>· Maintain system maintenance, which include backup of server\nand controllers, troubleshooting and fixing the faulty server & controller.</p><p>· Performing periodical Backup, Restoration, and using\nrecovery software.</p><p>· Basic knowledge Linux, SQL Server and MS Access<strong> </strong>databases.</p><p>· Maintain network switches & routers and Includes\nconfiguration.</p><p>· Managing Users, Privileges and Roles. </p><p>· Maintain cybersecurity standards, procedures, configurations\nfor the systems and services.</p><p>· Monitor and\nnotify security patches releases for the various products.</p><p>· Attend security incident response that includes understanding\nalerts, coordination with various system or service operators, identifying\npotential threats and performing basic triaging prior to escalation to next\nlevel security responder.</p><p>· Managing all maintenance breakdown and ensure all faults are\nattended.</p><p>· Supervise onsite installations, testing and commissioning.</p><p>· Conduct routine inspection of the premises.</p><p>· Site meeting and liaising client.<br /><br /><br /><u><strong>Requirements </strong></u></p><p>· Relevant University Degree in Information Technology or Computer Technology Engineering and equivalent with 3 years’ experience or relevant Diploma in Information Technology or Computer Technology Engineering and equivalent with 6 years’</p><p>· Class 2 or 3 licence holder will be advantage</p>",
